HEADWORD: Fleshed
<hw>Fleshed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Corpulent;
fat; having flesh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Glutted; satiated; initiated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Fleshed</qex> with slaughter.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flesher</ent>⟦br⟧
